If a huge requests come at the same time, by default all requests will be queued to be processed by client thread pool. Some of the requests may thread starvation, and if the client closes the request on timeout, the ambari-server's may have a lot of connections in CLOSE_WAIT state. QoSFilter can prevent from this situation.
